Treatment15U

2023-03-23

15U This is to compare the groups of the anoikis project that have been treated with 15U

## [1] TRUE
## [1] "abundance"           "counts"              "length"             
## [4] "countsFromAbundance"

This is for setting up the meta data and DESeq2 object so that you can do your analysis

counts <- counts(dds[ , ], normalized = TRUE)
write.csv(counts, "~/RNAseq_Anoikis/OV90/RNAseq/15U/counts_15U.csv")

This is going to tell you information about the results from running DESeq2

res <- results(dds, contrast= c("condition", "P0_15U", "P1_15U"))
summary(res)
## 
## out of 18726 with nonzero total read count
## adjusted p-value < 0.1
## LFC > 0 (up)       : 2494, 13%
## LFC < 0 (down)     : 2645, 14%
## outliers [1]       : 16, 0.085%
## low counts [2]     : 2528, 13%
## (mean count < 1)
## [1] see 'cooksCutoff' argument of ?results
## [2] see 'independentFiltering' argument of ?results

 EnhancedVolcano(res,
    lab = rownames(res),
    x = 'log2FoldChange',
    y = 'pvalue')
## Warning: One or more p-values is 0. Converting to 10^-1 * current lowest
## non-zero p-value...

You can set results to whatever you want to compare from the dds object; see documentation for more if you do not like what it auto selects/ you want more than what this did first Here is an example template. There’s a # in front of it so that it is not running

res_2 <- results(dds, contrast=c("condition","P0_15U","P1.1_15U"))
summary(res_2)
## 
## out of 18726 with nonzero total read count
## adjusted p-value < 0.1
## LFC > 0 (up)       : 2754, 15%
## LFC < 0 (down)     : 2949, 16%
## outliers [1]       : 16, 0.085%
## low counts [2]     : 2528, 13%
## (mean count < 1)
## [1] see 'cooksCutoff' argument of ?results
## [2] see 'independentFiltering' argument of ?results

 EnhancedVolcano(res_2,
    lab = rownames(res_2),
    x = 'log2FoldChange',
    y = 'pvalue')
## Warning: One or more p-values is 0. Converting to 10^-1 * current lowest
## non-zero p-value...
